{"_id":"283fa57d-0feb-404a-a614-872278a83818","type":"ability","name":"Known By Many Names","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/infiltration.svg","system":{"skill":"Infiltration","name":"Known By Many Names","rank":"3","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"1","description":"You have multiple false identities that you can switch between, keeping doctored credentials and appropriate clothing for each. You have a number of these identities equal to your Infiltration ranks, and you should come up with some details of each (such as an alias, profession, etc). It takes one minute and 1 Vim for you to change to one of these identities (no Vim cost to change back to your usual identity). You may swap out one identity for another during down time between Ventures.","roll_type":"none","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"infiltration"}}
{"_id":"54f4f01f-3957-4ffc-80e4-b9b40537d85b","type":"ability","name":"Security Expert","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/infiltration.svg","system":{"skill":"Infiltration","name":"Security Expert","rank":"3","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"2","description":"For the next hour, you automatically spot security systems before you encounter them. This only applies to constructed systems, not natural hazards.","roll_type":"none","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"infiltration"}}
{"_id":"842555c1-25a0-4aab-9e3a-5be0b7ec2959","type":"ability","name":"Vocal Mimic","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/infiltration.svg","system":{"skill":"Infiltration","name":"Vocal Mimic","rank":"3","type":"technique","action":"medium","defense":"intuition","target":"Single","range":"Short","duration":"","cost":"2","description":"You can alter your voice to mimic a specific individual, or throw your voice to make it appear as though it came from a specific point within a short range. Out of combat, this does not require Vim. In combat, you may use this to sow confusion in an enemy takes their orders from another. On a success, you choose how they act on their next turn. You may have them retreat --- moving as far from combat as they can, attack a specific target --- which must be one they consider an enemy, or do nothing --- giving them nonsensical orders. At the GM's discretion you may choose something else, however they will never attack their allies or put themselves in obvious avoidable danger.","roll_type":"","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"infiltration"}}
{"_id":"9a8268b0-97b1-42e0-bbf7-67fe81a98963","type":"ability","name":"Ghost Entry","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/infiltration.svg","system":{"skill":"Infiltration","name":"Ghost Entry","rank":"5","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"3","description":"Once per Venture, you may bypass a locked door, a guard, an alarm, or some other security system without leaving a trace and without needing a roll. Nobody but you knows how you managed it. This does not allow others to come with you, however it may make it easier for them (for example if the door can be unlocked from the other side).","roll_type":"none","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"infiltration"}}
{"_id":"c8e0d983-5cc0-416c-a856-b0717d241a69","type":"ability","name":"Master of Disguise","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/infiltration.svg","system":{"skill":"Infiltration","name":"Master of Disguise","rank":"5","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"intuition","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"2","description":"You can disguise yourself as a completely different person, even believably concealing your age and gender and altering your voice. You can even pass as a specific person to anyone not in your area, however you must make an Infiltration check if anyone who knows the person interacts with you in your area.","roll_type":"","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"infiltration"}}
{"_id":"cd91392d-8774-4fbe-b0ba-3d3ba06a3867","type":"ability","name":"Blend In","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/infiltration.svg","system":{"skill":"Infiltration","name":"Blend In","rank":"1","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"1","description":"With a minute of preparation, you can disguise yourself to blend into a setting as though you belong there. You gain a boon to all checks made to act without drawing attention. If you spend an hour preparing (finding believable disguises such as a uniform), you also gain a boon to all influence checks to interact with people in that setting.","roll_type":"none","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"infiltration"}}
{"_id":"d54e14bd-a833-4be0-bb62-82a4f816b525","type":"ability","name":"Master of Chaos","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/infiltration.svg","system":{"skill":"Infiltration","name":"Master of Chaos","rank":"5","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"2","description":"You orchestrate a distraction such as a malfunctioning alarm, a glitch in a clockwork eye, a small fire, or a similar event to cause a distraction typically lasting one to ten minutes (depending on what the distraction is). On a success, all your allies gain a boon to moving or acting unnoticed or to blending in for the duration of the distraction, however you take one Consequence.","roll_type":"","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"infiltration"}}
{"_id":"e08dd6c9-012e-48b5-9e19-4c2be05a800e","type":"ability","name":"Slip Away","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/infiltration.svg","system":{"skill":"Infiltration","name":"Slip Away","rank":"1","type":"technique","action":"reaction","defense":"intuition","target":"Single","range":"Adjacent","duration":"","cost":"2","description":"You Help your own Agility or Strength defense check when attacked by a creature in your area. If you successfully defend, you slip behind your target and gain a Boon on your next attack against them.","roll_type":"help","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"infiltration"}}
{"_id":"f38f5a83-6d7e-43bd-8a66-0c3383244da1","type":"ability","name":"Bypass","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/infiltration.svg","system":{"skill":"Infiltration","name":"Bypass","rank":"1","type":"ability","action":"","defense":"","target":"","range":"","duration":"","cost":"1","description":"This ability can be used when fail to disable a trap, alarm, or security system which will activate on a failure. Make a second check. If you succeed, you are able to bypass its activation but take a Consequence as your handiwork will be obvious to anyone who sees it (and the device is still active). Otherwise it activates as normal.","roll_type":"","domain":"Expertise","costtype":"vim","skill_id":"infiltration"}}
{"_id":"f731a294-2760-4dd1-9229-7a8a1f385b04","type":"skill","name":"Infiltration","img":"systems/venture-rpg/assets/skills/infiltration.svg","system":{"skill_id":"infiltration","domain":"Expertise","rank":1,"stat":"intuition","description":"The Infiltration skill is used to get into places you're not supposed to be. It is used to blend into crowds and disguise yourself, as well as to bypass security measures. It is not typically used for actively hiding yourself, which is the domain of the Stealth skill."}}
